HEADWORD: Awaken
<hw>A*wak"en</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t. & i.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Awakened</conjf> <pr>(<?/)</pr>;
<pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Awakening</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE.
<ets>awakenen</ets>, <ets>awaknen</ets>, AS. <ets>⟦amac⟧w⟦ae⟧cnan</ets>,
<ets>⟦amac⟧w⟦ae⟧cnian</ets>, v. i.; pref. <ets>on-</ets> +
<ets>w⟦ae⟧cnan</ets> to wake. Cf. <er>Awake</er>, <pos>v.
t.</pos>]</ety> <def>To rouse from sleep or torpor; to awake; to
wake.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[He] is dispatched⟦br⟧
Already to <qex>awaken</qex> whom thou nam'st.</q>
<rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Their consciences are thoroughly <qex>awakened</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Tillotson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To arouse; excite; stir up; call forth.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Awakener</ent>⟦br⟧
